## Add a storage

Uiza allows you to add storages (FTP, S3 - both private and AWS) to your application. Storages can be used for [creating entities](#create-entity).

> **Add a FTP Storage**

> REQUEST

```shell
curl -X POST \
  <%= config[:endpoint] %>/media/storage \
  -H 'Authorization: <%= config[:token] %>' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
    "name": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_name] %>",
    "description": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_description] %>",
    "storageType": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_storage_type] %>",
    "host": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_host] %>",
    "username": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_username] %>",
    "password": "<%= config[:storage_add_fpt_password] %>",
    "port": <%= config[:storage_add_fpt_port] %>
}'
```

